Package: foundry-linux-blender
Version: 1.0.0
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Foundry Linux <packages@foundrylinux.org>
Section: metapackages
Priority: optional
Depends: blender (>= 4.2),
 python3,
 foundry-linux-engine-build-deps
Recommends: foundry-linux-blender-addon
Homepage: https://foundrylinux.org/develop/blender/
Description: Blender 4.2+ configured for World Foundry level authoring
 Pulls in Blender 4.2 (from the Blender PPA — the snap is unsuitable
 because its sandbox blocks the debug-bridge TCP port the WF addon
 uses) plus the Python and build toolchain required to build the
 wf_core.so native module shipped with the wf_blender addon.
 .
 The addon itself is in foundry-linux-blender-addon (Recommends, not
 Depends, so you can build it from source if you prefer).
